cycles will sample the \'data\' input to form the `delay[3:0]` value. \\n4. **Timer Logic**: The timer counts for `(delay + 1) * 1000` cycles. I will use a large counter (at least 14 bits since 16 * 1000 = 16000) to track the total cycles. To output the current `count` (the delay value), I will use a secondary counter that decrements every 1000 cycles.\\n5. **State Transitions**: \\n   - `SEARCH`: Look for 1101.\\n   - `LOAD_DELAY`: Shift in 4 bits.\\n   - `COUNTING`: Decrement the large timer and the `count` output.\\n   - `DONE`: Assert `done` and wait for `ack`.\\n6. **Timing details**: The requirement says: \'delay for 1000 cycles, then delay-1 for 1000 cycles... until it is 0 for 1000 cycles\'. This means the total duration is `(delay + 1) * 1000`. For `delay=0`, duration is 1000 cycles where `count=0`.\\n7. **Advice to avoid syntax errors**: \\n   - Always use `always @(*)` for combinational logic to avoid missing signals in the sensitivity list.\\n   - Ensure all ports and signals are declared as `logic`.\\n   - When using `case` statements, ensure all possible states are covered or include a `default` case.\\n   - Be careful with bit-widths; a counter for 16,000 cycles must be at least 14 bits (2^14 = 16384).",\n    "module": "module TopModule(\\n    input  logic       clk,\\n    input  logic       reset,\\n    input  logic       data,\\n    output logic [3:0] count,\\n    output logic       counting,\\n    output logic       done,\\n    input  logic       ack\\n);\\n\\n    // State Definitions\\n    localparam STATE_SEARCH     = 4\'d0;\\n    localparam STATE_LOAD_DELAY = 4\'d1;\\n    localparam STATE_COUNTING   = 4\'d2;\\n    localparam STATE_DONE       = 4\'d3;\\n\\n    logic [3:0] state;\\n    logic [3:0] pattern_shift;\\n    logic [3:0] delay_reg;\\n    logic [3:0] delay_shift_cnt;\\n    logic [3:0] delay_bits_reg;\\n    \\n    // Timer counters\\n    // Max delay is 15. Total cycles = (15+1)*1000 = 16000. \\n    // 14 bits is enough (2^14 = 16384).\\n    logic [13:0] timer_cnt;\\n    logic [13:0] timer_limit;\\n    logic [3:0]  current_count_out;\\n\\n    // Sequential Logic\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset) begin\\n            state <= STATE_SEARCH;\\n            pattern_shift <= 4\'b0;\\n            delay_reg <= 4\'b0;\\n            delay_shift_cnt <= 4\'b0;\\n            delay_bits_reg <= 4\'b0;\\n            timer_cnt <= 14\'d0;\\n            timer_limit <= 14\'d0;\\n            current_count_out <= 4\'d0;\\n        end else begin\\n            case (state)n\\n                STATE_SEARCH:\\n                    begin\\n                        pattern_shift <= {pattern_shift[2:0], data};\\n                        if ({pattern_shift[2:0], data} == 4\'b1101) begin\\n                            state <= STATE_LOAD_DELAY;\\n                            delay_shift_cnt <= 4\'d0;\\n                            delay_bits_reg <= 4\'b0;\\n                        end else begin\\n                            state <= STATE_SEARCH;\\n                        end\\n                    end\\n\\n                STATE_LOAD_DELAY:\\n                    begin\\n                        // Shift in 4 bits, MSB first\\n                        delay_bits_reg <= {delay_bits_reg[2:0], data};\\n                        if (delay_shift_cnt == 4\'d3) begin\\n                            delay_reg <= {delay_bits_reg[2:0], data};\\n                            state <= STATE_COUNTING;\\n                            delay_shift_cnt <= 4\'d0;\\n                            // Prepare timer\\n                            // Total cycles = (delay + 1) * 1000\\n                            // We count from 0 to (delay+1)*1000 - 1\\n                            timer_limit <= ( {1\'b0, ({delay_bits_reg[2:0], data} + 4\'d1)} * 14\'d1000 ) - 14\'d1;\\n                            timer_cnt <= 14\'d0;\\n                            current_count_out <= {delay_bits_reg[2:0], data};\\n                        end else begin\\n                            delay_shift_cnt <= delay_shift_cnt + 4\'d1;\\n                        end\\n                    end\\n\\n                STATE_COUNTING:\\n                    begin\\n                        if (timer_cnt < timer_limit) begin\\n                            timer_cnt <= timer_cnt + 14\'d1;\\n                            // Every 1000 cycles, decrement the display count\\n                            // We use (timer_cnt + 1) % 1000 == 0 to detect the 1000th cycle\\n                            if ((timer_cnt + 14\'d1) % 14\'d1000 == 14\'d0) begin\\n                                if (current_count_out > 4\'d0) begin\\n                                    current_count_out <= current_count_out - 4\'d1;\\n                                end\\n                            end\\n                        end else begin\\n                            state <= STATE_DONE;\\n                            timer_cnt <= 14\'d0;\\n                        end\\n                    end\\n\\n                STATE_DONE:\\n                    begin\\n                        if (ack) begin\\n                            state <= STATE_SEARCH;\\n                            pattern_shift <= 4\'b0;\\n                        end else begin\\n                            state <= STATE_DONE;\\n                        end\\n                    end\\n\\n                default:\\n                    state <= STATE_SEARCH;\\n            endcase\\n        end\\n    end\\n\\n    // Output assignments\\n    assign counting = (state == STATE_COUNTING);\\n    assign done     = (state == STATE_DONE);\\n    assign count    = (state == STATE_COUNTING) ? current_count_out : 4\'b0;\\n\\nendmodule"\n}')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nThe error below has been reported by the format tool:\n<format_error>\n{\n    "stdout": "",\n    "stderr": "./output_t22_gemma4_26b_full_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob156_review2015_fancytimer/rtl.s